    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_42180_1833_09_27_page01.jpg"/>
                <opener>
                    <dateline><!--If there's no date line, remove this element. Record in the order in which it is written on the letter.-->
                        <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE"/><choice><orig>Edgeworth town</orig><reg>Edgeworthstown</reg></choice>
                        <date when="1833-09-27">Sep<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>. 27<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. 1833</date></dateline>
                    <salute><choice><orig>D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi></orig><reg>Dear</reg></choice>. Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    I wrote to you on the 6<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> <unclear>Ins<hi rend="superscript">t</hi></unclear><lb/>
                    to inquire whether you<lb/>
                    had or had not put the<lb/>
                    drawings I sent you into<lb/>
                    the hands of an engraver<lb/>
                    If you have not I beg '<lb/>
                    you will not <add>put the chimney sweeper <hi rend="underline">in hand</hi></add> - because<lb/>
                    I have changed my <choice><orig>pur-<lb/>
                    pose</orig><reg>purpose</reg></choice> as to the story I spoke<lb/>
                    of to you and I now<lb/>
                    beg you to understand<lb/>
                    that it will not be a story<lb/>
                    for young children and<lb/>
                    short as the Snow woman<lb/>
                    The subject has spread<lb/>
                    out under my hands<lb/>
                    and it will be more of<lb/>
                    a moral &amp; popular tale<lb/>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <!--More body paragraphs as needed.--></p>
                <p>
                    <!--More body paragraphs as needed.-->
                    <!--Where there's a page break record it inside the relevant body paragraph like this, 
                  with the self-closing page-break element. n="2" indicates the START of the second page.-->
                    <pb n="2" facs="image2.jpg"/>
                </p>
                <p><!--More body paragraphs as needed.--></p>
                <closer>
                    <!--include linebreaks, if used. example: <closer> Yours<lb/> Very sincerely<lb/> -->
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p><!--A postscript goes here, outside the <closer>. --></p>
                </postscript>
                <!--You can include a <pb/> here, or inside the postScript.-->
                <!-- Format for postscripts. 
               Postscripts do NOT go inside closer tags. Adjust to take into account the order in your letter. 
               Sometimes the signature is on page three, the address on page four, then the postscript follows back on the top of page one, for example.-->
